                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2537: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-09T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 9, 1931—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 9—7:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>288. Upon Sugimura’s return to Geneva I learn that Yoshizawa made the proposal
                    outlined in my number 287, November 7, 11 a.m., his own and so telegraphed it to
                    Tokyo. It is now being referred to as the “Yoshizawa proposal.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
